[The above alert message, signed by Dr Juan Lubroth, Chief Veterinary Officer, Animal Health Service, Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO), Rome, was distributed by email to the CVO's in the Eastern Africa countries on [Fri 29 Jun 2018]. This alert message is not available on-line; we are grateful to FAO's Dr Pinto for forwarding this useful document upon ProMED-mail's request. Its actuality is retained.

Since the official confirmation of RVF in the country (on Fri 8 Jun 2018), Kenya officially notified a total of 6 outbreaks in Wajir (n=2), Isiolo (n=2), Tana River (n=1) and Siaya (n=1) counties.

According to a reliable source, the number of Kenya's counties where RVF has been confirmed in animals since the start of the event exceeds the said 4. The most recent follow-up report was submitted to the OIE on [Mon 2 Jul 2018]. A summary with links to the reports and a map is available at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=26827.

Livestock ring vaccination in the affected areas is on-going. The ban on movement and slaughter of animals from affected and at-risk counties remains in place. - Mod.AS

